# S19-T5: Feedback panel or badges (board / instance)
# S19-T5-FeedbackPanelOrBadges.pd

**Objective:** Surface AI feedback at board or instance level so the human can see there is feedback without opening every task. Options: (a) badge on task card (e.g. "1" or icon when task has feedback, especially type=block); (b) a small "AI feedback" panel or drawer listing recent feedback for current sprint/instance with links to task. Implement at least one so the human discovers feedback easily.

**Context:**
- S19-T4: task detail shows feedback for one task. Board view and instance view need a way to show "you have N AI messages" or "block on task X". S12/S10: "waiting for human" already exists for gate; AI feedback can add "Agent says: waiting for LGTM" on the same task.
- S05/S06: badge or panel uses existing glass; no new layout break.

**Gate:** OPEN

**requires:** [BUILD]

**Steps:**
1. Option A — Badges on task cards: when loading board data, fetch feedback counts (or feedback list) for the sprint; for each task that has feedback (or has type=block), show a small badge on the task card (e.g. dot or "1"). Click opens task detail where full feedback is shown. Option B — Feedback panel: a collapsible panel or drawer (e.g. "AI feedback") that lists recent feedback for current instance or sprint; each item links to the task (or opens task detail). Choose one or both; document.
2. Implement chosen option(s). Use GET /api/feedback with sprintId or instanceId to get list; aggregate by task if needed for badges. Panel can show last N items with task title and feedback body preview.
3. Optional: highlight or sort by type=block so "blocking" feedback is visible first. Handle empty (no panel or no badges when no feedback). S05/S06 preserved.
4. Ensure realtime or refresh: when new feedback arrives (if realtime server or poll), update badges or panel. Optional for this task; can be follow-up.

**Acceptance Criteria:**
- Board or instance view surfaces AI feedback (badges on cards and/or feedback panel). Human can see that feedback exists and reach it. S05/S06 preserved.
